{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# trnL Reference Database Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook builds a plant trnL reference database trimmed to sequences amplified by the trnLg/trnLh primer pair, combining RefSeq plastid genomes (downloaded locally) and GenBank sequences queried remotely via NCBI.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running:** update the paths in the Configuration cell below to match your cluster environment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Configuration\n",
    "\n",
    "Set all paths and cluster parameters here. These variables are reused throughout the notebook."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── User-defined paths ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "SCRATCH      <- \"/scratch/your_username\"               # cluster scratch directory\n",
    "REPO_DIR     <- \"/path/to/food-dbs\"                    # cloned repo location\n",
    "PLASTID_DIR  <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"plastid_refseq\")   # RefSeq download destination\n",
    "SQL_PATH     <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"accessionTaxa.sql\") # taxonomizr SQL database\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── SLURM parameters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "PARTITION    <- \"general\"   # partition/queue name on your cluster\n",
    "R_MODULE     <- \"R/4.3.0\"   # module name: check with 'module avail R'\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Configuration set.\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Repo:    \", REPO_DIR, \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Scratch: \", SCRATCH, \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Install R packages (one-time setup)\n",
    "\n",
    "Run this cell once on first use. Safe to skip on subsequent runs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pkgs <- c(\"Biostrings\", \"ShortRead\")  # Bioconductor\n",
    "bioc_pkgs <- c(\"Biostrings\", \"ShortRead\")\n",
    "cran_pkgs <- c(\"taxonomizr\", \"tidyverse\", \"rentrez\", \"here\", \"MButils\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if (!requireNamespace(\"BiocManager\", quietly = TRUE))\n",
    "    install.packages(\"BiocManager\")\n",
    "\n",
    "BiocManager::install(bioc_pkgs, ask = FALSE)\n",
    "install.packages(cran_pkgs, repos = \"https://cloud.r-project.org\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Package installation complete.\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Submit SLURM job: Download RefSeq plastid sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "This writes a SLURM script and submits it. The job downloads all RefSeq plastid FASTA files and concatenates them into a single file. Typically takes 1–3 hours depending on cluster network speed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "download_script <- paste0(\n",
    "\"#!/bin/bash\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --job-name=refseq_download\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --partition=\", PARTITION, \"\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --time=04:00:00\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --mem=8G\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --cpus-per-task=2\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --output=\", SCRATCH, \"/refseq_download.log\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"mkdir -p \", PLASTID_DIR, \"\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"# Download all plastid genomic FASTA files from RefSeq FTP\n\",\n",
    "\"wget -r -nd -A '*.genomic.fna.gz' \\\\\n\",\n",
    "\"  ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/refseq/release/plastid/ \\\\\n\",\n",
    "\"  -P \", PLASTID_DIR, \"\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"# Decompress and combine into a single FASTA\n\",\n",
    "\"zcat \", PLASTID_DIR, \"/*.genomic.fna.gz > \", PLASTID_DIR, \"/refseq_plastid_all.fasta\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"echo 'Download and decompression complete.'\n\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "script_path <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"download_refseq.sh\")\n",
    "writeLines(download_script, script_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "result <- system(paste(\"sbatch\", script_path), intern = TRUE)\n",
    "cat(result, \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract job ID for monitoring\n",
    "download_job_id <- gsub(\"[^0-9]\", \"\", result)\n",
    "cat(\"Download job ID:\", download_job_id, \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Submit SLURM job: Build taxonomizr SQL database\n",
    "\n",
    "Downloads NCBI taxonomy dumps and builds the SQLite index used for accession → taxonomy lookups. Requires ~70 GB disk space and typically takes several hours. This job can run in parallel with the RefSeq download."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "taxonomizr_script <- paste0(\n",
    "\"#!/bin/bash\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --job-name=taxonomizr_build\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --partition=\", PARTITION, \"\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --time=12:00:00\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --mem=16G\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --cpus-per-task=4\n\",\n",
    "\"#SBATCH --output=\", SCRATCH, \"/taxonomizr_build.log\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"module load \", R_MODULE, \"\n\",\n",
    "\"\n\",\n",
    "\"Rscript -e \\\"\n\",\n",
    \"  library(taxonomizr)\n\",\n",
    \"  prepareDatabase('\", SQL_PATH, \"')\n\",\n",
    \"  cat('taxonomizr database built.\\\\n')\n\",\n",
    "\"\\\"\n\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "tax_script_path <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"build_taxonomizr.sh\")\n",
    "writeLines(taxonomizr_script, tax_script_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "result <- system(paste(\"sbatch\", tax_script_path), intern = TRUE)\n",
    "cat(result, \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "taxonomizr_job_id <- gsub(\"[^0-9]\", \"\", result)\n",
    "cat(\"taxonomizr job ID:\", taxonomizr_job_id, \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Monitor job status\n",
    "\n",
    "Re-run this cell to check whether the download and taxonomizr jobs have finished. Proceed to section 5 once both show no output (i.e., they have completed and left the queue)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "status <- system(\"squeue --me --format='%.18i %.9P %.30j %.8T %.10M %.6D %R'\", intern = TRUE)\n",
    "cat(paste(status, collapse = \"\\n\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check log files for errors\n",
    "download_log <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"refseq_download.log\")\n",
    "tax_log      <- file.path(SCRATCH, \"taxonomizr_build.log\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if (file.exists(download_log)) {\n",
    "    cat(\"\\n--- Last 5 lines of download log ---\\n\")\n",
    "    cat(paste(tail(readLines(download_log), 5), collapse = \"\\n\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "if (file.exists(tax_log)) {\n",
    "    cat(\"\\n--- Last 5 lines of taxonomizr log ---\\n\")\n",
    "    cat(paste(tail(readLines(tax_log), 5), collapse = \"\\n\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Filter RefSeq to one sequence per species\n",
    "\n",
    "The combined RefSeq FASTA contains multiple entries per species. This step retains one representative sequence per species, matching the format expected by the pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "library(Biostrings)\n",
    "library(ShortRead)\n",
    "library(tidyverse)\n",
    "\n",
    "plastid_all_path     <- file.path(PLASTID_DIR, \"refseq_plastid_all.fasta\")\n",
    "plastid_species_path <- file.path(PLASTID_DIR, \"refseq_plastid_species.fasta\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Reading combined RefSeq FASTA...\\n\")\n",
    "plastid <- readDNAStringSet(plastid_all_path)\n",
    "cat(length(plastid), \"total sequences\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract species name (first two words after accession in header)\n",
    "species <- sub(\"^\\\\S+\\\\s+(\\\\S+\\\\s+\\\\S+).*\", \"\\\\1\", names(plastid))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep first occurrence of each species (RefSeq ordering is consistent)\n",
    "keep <- !duplicated(species)\n",
    "plastid_species <- plastid[keep]\n",
    "names(plastid_species) <- species[keep]\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(plastid_species), \"unique species retained\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "writeXStringSet(plastid_species, plastid_species_path)\n",
    "cat(\"Saved to\", plastid_species_path, \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Load libraries and source functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "library(Biostrings)\n",
    "library(ShortRead)\n",
    "library(taxonomizr)\n",
    "library(tidyverse)\n",
    "library(rentrez)\n",
    "\n",
    "source(file.path(REPO_DIR, \"code\", \"functions\", \"find_primer_pair.R\"))\n",
    "source(file.path(REPO_DIR, \"code\", \"functions\", \"query_ncbi.R\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Libraries and functions loaded.\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Load input data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# trnL g/h primer sequences\n",
    "trnLG <- DNAString(\"GGGCAATCCTGAGCCAA\")\n",
    "trnLH <- DNAString(\"CCATTGAGTCTCTGCACCTATC\")\n",
    "primers <- list(trnLG, trnLH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Curated food plant list\n",
    "plants <-\n",
    "    file.path(REPO_DIR, \"data\", \"inputs\", \"human-foods.csv\") |>\n",
    "    read.csv(stringsAsFactors = FALSE) |>\n",
    "    filter(category == \"plant\") |>\n",
    "    pull(scientific_name)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(plants), \"food plant species loaded\\n\")\n",
    "head(plants)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Manual curation edits (omissions and renamings)\n",
    "edits <-\n",
    "    file.path(REPO_DIR, \"data\", \"inputs\", \"Manual renaming.csv\") |>\n",
    "    read_csv()\n",
    "\n",
    "edits"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# RefSeq plastid sequences (one per species, produced in section 5)\n",
    "plastid_species_path <- file.path(PLASTID_DIR, \"refseq_plastid_species.fasta\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plastid <- readDNAStringSet(plastid_species_path)\n",
    "cat(length(plastid), \"RefSeq plastid species loaded\\n\")\n",
    "plastid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. RefSeq: find primer binding sites and trim"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove sequences with Ns before primer search\n",
    "cat(\"Before cleaning:\", length(plastid), \"sequences\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"After cleaning: \", length(clean(plastid)), \"sequences\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "refseq.trnL <- find_primer_pair(plastid,\n",
    "                                fwd = primers[[1]],\n",
    "                                rev = primers[[2]])\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(refseq.trnL), \"sequences contain the trnL g/h primer pair\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Subset to food plants\n",
    "plants.i <- lapply(plants, grep, x = names(refseq.trnL)) |> unlist()\n",
    "refseq.trnL <- refseq.trnL[plants.i]\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(refseq.trnL), \"food plant trnL sequences from RefSeq\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strip names to accession only\n",
    "names(refseq.trnL) <- gsub(names(refseq.trnL),\n",
    "                           pattern = \" .*$\",\n",
    "                           replacement = \"\")\n",
    "head(names(refseq.trnL))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. NCBI GenBank: remote query"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Query NCBI nucleotide database for trnL sequences across all food plants\n",
    "# Chunked into groups of 50 species to avoid HTTP failures\n",
    "cat(\"Querying NCBI... this may take 10-30 minutes\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ncbi.trnL <- query_ncbi(marker = \"trnL\", organisms = plants)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(ncbi.trnL), \"sequences returned from NCBI\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Find primer binding sites in NCBI sequences\n",
    "ncbi.trnL <- find_primer_pair(ncbi.trnL,\n",
    "                              fwd = primers[[1]],\n",
    "                              rev = primers[[2]])\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(length(ncbi.trnL), \"sequences contain the trnL g/h primer pair\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove unverified sequences\n",
    "n_before <- length(ncbi.trnL)\n",
    "ncbi.trnL <- ncbi.trnL[!grepl(\"UNVERIFIED\", names(ncbi.trnL))]\n",
    "cat(\"Removed\", n_before - length(ncbi.trnL), \"unverified sequences\\n\")\n",
    "cat(length(ncbi.trnL), \"sequences remaining\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strip names to accession only\n",
    "names(ncbi.trnL) <-\n",
    "    names(ncbi.trnL) |>\n",
    "    gsub(pattern = \" .+$\", replacement = \"\") |>\n",
    "    gsub(pattern = \"^>\", replacement = \"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "head(names(ncbi.trnL))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Combine RefSeq and GenBank sequences"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check overlap between sources\n",
    "cat(\"RefSeq sequences: \",  length(refseq.trnL), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"GenBank sequences:\",  length(ncbi.trnL),   \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Shared accessions: \", intersect(names(ncbi.trnL), names(refseq.trnL)) |> length(), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"RefSeq-only:       \", setdiff(names(refseq.trnL), names(ncbi.trnL))   |> length(), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"GenBank-only:      \", setdiff(names(ncbi.trnL), names(refseq.trnL))   |> length(), \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build combined data frame (GenBank rows first; RefSeq appended)\n",
    "seqs.df <-\n",
    "    bind_rows(\n",
    "        data.frame(source    = \"GenBank\",\n",
    "                   accession = names(ncbi.trnL),\n",
    "                   seq       = as.character(ncbi.trnL)),\n",
    "        data.frame(source    = \"RefSeq\",\n",
    "                   accession = names(refseq.trnL),\n",
    "                   seq       = as.character(refseq.trnL))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(nrow(seqs.df), \"total sequences before deduplication\\n\")\n",
    "head(seqs.df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fetch and trim manual additions from curation file\n",
    "additions <- filter(edits, type == \"add\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if (nrow(additions) > 0) {\n",
    "    cat(\"Fetching\", nrow(additions), \"manual addition(s) from NCBI...\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    seqs_raw <-\n",
    "        entrez_fetch(db = \"nucleotide\",\n",
    "                     id = additions$accession,\n",
    "                     rettype = \"fasta\") |>\n",
    "        strsplit(\"\\n{2,}\") |>\n",
    "        unlist()\n",
    "\n",
    "    ex   <- \"[^>]\\\\S*\"\n",
    "    accs <- str_extract(seqs_raw, ex)\n",
    "    seqs_only <-\n",
    "        seqs_raw |>\n",
    "        sub(\"^[^\\n]*\\n\", \"\", x = _) |>\n",
    "        gsub(\"\\n\", \"\", x = _)\n",
    "\n",
    "    manual_seqs <- DNAStringSet(seqs_only)\n",
    "    names(manual_seqs) <- accs\n",
    "\n",
    "    manual_seqs <- find_primer_pair(manual_seqs,\n",
    "                                   fwd = primers[[1]],\n",
    "                                   rev = primers[[2]])\n",
    "\n",
    "    seqs.df <- bind_rows(\n",
    "        data.frame(seq = as.character(manual_seqs), accession = names(manual_seqs)),\n",
    "        seqs.df\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    cat(\"Manual additions appended.\\n\")\n",
    "} else {\n",
    "    cat(\"No manual additions in curation file.\\n\")\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. Taxonomy lookup via taxonomizr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cat(\"Looking up taxonomy for\", nrow(seqs.df), \"accessions...\\n\")\n",
    "ids <- taxonomizr::accessionToTaxa(seqs.df$accession, SQL_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Missing taxonomy IDs:\", sum(is.na(ids)), \"\\n\")\n",
    "if (any(is.na(ids))) {\n",
    "    cat(\"Accessions with missing IDs:\\n\")\n",
    "    print(seqs.df[is.na(ids), c(\"source\", \"accession\")])\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# If any IDs are missing, manually assign them here.\n",
    "# These are sequences added to NCBI after the SQL database was built.\n",
    "# Look up the taxon ID at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy\n",
    "# Example (from the original workflow):\n",
    "#   ids[12] <- 3747   # OP764691.1 Fragaria x ananassa\n",
    "\n",
    "# Confirm all resolved\n",
    "cat(\"Remaining missing IDs:\", sum(is.na(ids)), \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pull full taxonomy for all taxon IDs\n",
    "taxonomy.raw <- taxonomizr::getRawTaxonomy(ids, SQL_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "vars <- c(\"superkingdom\", \"phylum\", \"class\", \"order\",\n",
    "          \"family\", \"genus\", \"species\", \"subspecies\", \"varietas\", \"forma\")\n",
    "\n",
    "taxonomy <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = length(vars), nrow = 0))\n",
    "colnames(taxonomy) <- vars\n",
    "\n",
    "for (i in seq_along(taxonomy.raw)) {\n",
    "    row.i <- taxonomy.raw[[i]] |> t() |> data.frame()\n",
    "    shared <- intersect(vars, names(row.i))\n",
    "    row.i  <- select(row.i, one_of(shared))\n",
    "    taxonomy <- bind_rows(taxonomy, row.i)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "taxonomy$taxid <- names(taxonomy.raw) |> trimws() |> as.integer()\n",
    "taxonomy <- select(taxonomy, taxid, everything())\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df <- bind_cols(seqs.df, taxonomy)\n",
    "cat(\"Taxonomy joined.\\n\")\n",
    "head(seqs.df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 12. Manual curation edits"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Omissions: remove sequences flagged as likely mislabelled\n",
    "omit <- filter(edits, type == \"omit\")\n",
    "seqs.df <- filter(seqs.df, !(accession %in% omit$accession & seq %in% omit$sequence))\n",
    "cat(\"After omissions:\", nrow(seqs.df), \"sequences\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Renamings: update varietas for Brassica oleracea subspecies\n",
    "seqs.df$varietas[seqs.df$accession == \"AB213010.1\"] <- \"Brassica oleracea var. capitata\"\n",
    "seqs.df$varietas[seqs.df$accession == \"AC183493.1\"] <- \"Brassica oleracea var. alboglabra\"\n",
    "seqs.df$varietas[seqs.df$accession == \"LR031874.1\"] <- \"Brassica oleracea var. italica\"\n",
    "seqs.df$varietas[seqs.df$accession == \"LR031875.1\"] <- \"Brassica oleracea var. italica\"\n",
    "seqs.df$varietas[seqs.df$accession == \"LR031876.1\"] <- \"Brassica oleracea var. italica\"\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Renaming edits applied.\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Assign lowest available taxonomic level as the taxon name\n",
    "seqs.df <-\n",
    "    seqs.df |>\n",
    "    MButils::lowest_level() |>\n",
    "    rename(taxon = \"name\") |>\n",
    "    select(source, accession, taxon, taxid, superkingdom:forma, seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "head(seqs.df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 13. Quality control"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Flag sequences containing degenerate (non-ACGT) characters\n",
    "seqs.df$N <- grepl(\"[AGCT]*[^AGCT]+\", seqs.df$seq)\n",
    "cat(sum(seqs.df$N), \"sequences contain degenerate nucleotides\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Report taxa affected, and whether a clean backup sequence exists\n",
    "with_n <- seqs.df$taxon[seqs.df$N] |> unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df |>\n",
    "    filter(taxon %in% with_n) |>\n",
    "    group_by(taxon, N) |>\n",
    "    count() |>\n",
    "    ungroup() |>\n",
    "    group_by(taxon) |>\n",
    "    summarize(has_clean_backup = any(!N)) |>\n",
    "    arrange(has_clean_backup)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove sequences with degenerate nucleotides\n",
    "seqs.df <- filter(seqs.df, !grepl(\"[AGCT]*[^AGCT]+\", seq))\n",
    "cat(nrow(seqs.df), \"sequences after removing degenerate sequences\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 14. Standardise sequence orientation\n",
    "\n",
    "Sequences may be stored in either orientation in NCBI. This step detects reversed sequences and replaces them with their reverse complement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fwd_err <- floor(0.2 * length(trnLG))\n",
    "rev_err <- floor(0.2 * length(trnLH))\n",
    "\n",
    "ref <- DNAStringSet(seqs.df$seq)\n",
    "names(ref) <- paste(seqs.df$accession, seqs.df$taxon)\n",
    "\n",
    "fwd_matches <-\n",
    "    vmatchPattern(trnLG, ref, max.mismatch = fwd_err, fixed = TRUE) |>\n",
    "    as.data.frame() |>\n",
    "    filter(start <= 1) |>\n",
    "    mutate(type = \"forward\") |>\n",
    "    select(group, type)\n",
    "\n",
    "rev_matches <-\n",
    "    vmatchPattern(trnLH, ref, max.mismatch = rev_err, fixed = TRUE) |>\n",
    "    as.data.frame() |>\n",
    "    filter(start <= 1) |>\n",
    "    mutate(type = \"reverse\") |>\n",
    "    select(group, type)\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df <-\n",
    "    bind_rows(fwd_matches, rev_matches) |>\n",
    "    arrange(group) |>\n",
    "    bind_cols(seqs.df)\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df |> group_by(type) |> count()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Replace reversed sequences with their reverse complement\n",
    "seqs.df <-\n",
    "    mutate(seqs.df,\n",
    "           seq = ifelse(type == \"reverse\",\n",
    "                        yes = seq |> DNAStringSet() |> reverseComplement() |> as.character(),\n",
    "                        no  = seq)) |>\n",
    "    select(-c(type, group))\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Orientation standardised.\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 15. Deduplicate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Count duplicates per taxon (same species, same sequence)\n",
    "dups <- seqs.df |>\n",
    "    group_by(taxon) |>\n",
    "    summarize(n_dups = sum(duplicated(seq)))\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(\"Total duplicate sequences to remove:\", sum(dups$n_dups), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Expected sequences after deduplication:\", nrow(seqs.df) - sum(dups$n_dups), \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "seqs.df <-\n",
    "    seqs.df |>\n",
    "    group_by(superkingdom, phylum, class, order, family,\n",
    "             genus, species, subspecies, varietas, forma, taxon, seq) |>\n",
    "    arrange(desc(source), accession) |>  # RefSeq accessions take priority\n",
    "    summarize(accession = first(accession), .groups = \"drop\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cat(nrow(seqs.df), \"sequences after deduplication\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 16. Save outputs\n",
    "\n",
    "### DADA2-compatible"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dada2_dir <- file.path(REPO_DIR, \"data\", \"outputs\", \"dada2-compatible\", \"trnL\")\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df <- arrange(seqs.df, taxon, accession)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sequence file: accession + taxon name\n",
    "trnL <- DNAStringSet(seqs.df$seq)\n",
    "names(trnL) <- paste(seqs.df$accession, seqs.df$taxon)\n",
    "\n",
    "writeXStringSet(trnL, file.path(dada2_dir, \"trnLGH.fasta\"))\n",
    "cat(\"Saved trnLGH.fasta\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Taxonomy file: full lineage as semicolon-separated string\n",
    "seqs.df_tax <- seqs.df |>\n",
    "    unite(col = \"name\", superkingdom:forma, sep = \";\")\n",
    "\n",
    "names(trnL) <- seqs.df_tax$name\n",
    "writeXStringSet(trnL, file.path(dada2_dir, \"trnLGH_taxonomy.fasta\"))\n",
    "cat(\"Saved trnLGH_taxonomy.fasta\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### QIIME2-compatible"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "qiime2_dir <- file.path(REPO_DIR, \"data\", \"outputs\", \"qiime2-compatible\", \"trnL\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# QIIME2 requires unique accessions\n",
    "seqs.df_tax <- mutate(seqs.df_tax,\n",
    "                      acc = make.unique(accession, sep = \"_\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "names(trnL) <- seqs.df_tax$acc\n",
    "writeXStringSet(trnL, file.path(qiime2_dir, \"trnL-sequences.fasta\"))\n",
    "cat(\"Saved trnL-sequences.fasta\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "seqs.df_tax |>\n",
    "    select(`Feature ID` = acc, Taxon = name) |>\n",
    "    write_delim(file.path(qiime2_dir, \"trnL-taxonomy.tsv\"), delim = \"\\t\")\n",
    "cat(\"Saved trnL-taxonomy.tsv\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 17. Summary"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cat(\"=== trnL Reference Database Build Complete ===\\n\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Total sequences:  \", nrow(seqs.df), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Unique taxa:      \", n_distinct(seqs.df$taxon), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\"Source breakdown:\\n\")\n",
    "print(table(seqs.df$source))\n",
    "cat(\"\\nOutputs written to:\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\" \", file.path(dada2_dir,  \"trnLGH.fasta\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\" \", file.path(dada2_dir,  \"trnLGH_taxonomy.fasta\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\" \", file.path(qiime2_dir, \"trnL-sequences.fasta\"), \"\\n\")\n",
    "cat(\" \", file.path(qiime2_dir, \"trnL-taxonomy.tsv\"), \"\\n\")"
   ]
  }
